title: The Dark Knight (2008)
description: When the menace known as the Joker emerges, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

title: Mad Max: Fury Road (2015)
description: In a post-apocalyptic wasteland, Max teams up with Furiosa to flee a cult leader and his army in a massive tanker truck, battling across the desert.

title: Gladiator (2000)
description: A former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.

title: The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King (2003)
description: Gandalf and Aragorn lead the World of Men against Sauron's armies to draw his gaze from Frodo and Sam as they approach Mount Doom with the One Ring.

title: Superbad (2007)
description: Two high-school friends try to enjoy their final days together before heading off to different colleges, leading to a wildly awkward night of parties and mishaps.

title: The Big Sick (2017)
description: Based on a true story: a Pakistani-born comedian navigates cultural differences with his girlfriend when she falls seriously ill.

title: The Departed (2006)
description: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

title: No Country for Old Men (2007)
description: Violence and mayhem ensue after a hunter stumbles upon a drug deal gone wrong and more than two million dollars in cash.

title: The Social Network (2010)
description: Harvard student Mark Zuckerberg creates the social networking site that would become Facebook but faces lawsuits from co-founders.

title: There Will Be Blood (2007)
description: At the turn of the 20th century, a silver miner-turned-oilman expands his empire through ruthlessness and obsession, wreaking havoc on everyone around him.

title: Pan's Labyrinth (2006)
description: In post-Civil War Spain, a young girl discovers a mysterious labyrinth and a faun who sets her on a quest to prove her innocence.

title: Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone (2001)
description: An orphaned boy learns he is a wizard on his 11th birthday and attends Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry, uncovering a dark secret.

title: Get Out (2017)
description: A young African-American man visits his white girlfriend's parents only to uncover a disturbing secret beneath the surface.

title: A Quiet Place (2018)
description: In a post-apocalyptic world, a family must live in silence while hiding from creatures that hunt by sound.

title: Zodiac (2007)
description: In the late 1960s and 1970s, a San Francisco cartoonist becomes an amateur detective obsessed with tracking down the Zodiac Killer.

title: Gone Girl (2014)
description: On his fifth wedding anniversary, a man reports that his wife has gone missing; as the media frenzy grows, shocking secrets begin to emerge.

title: La La Land (2016)
description: While pursuing their dreams in Los Angeles, an aspiring actress and a jazz musician fall in love but struggle to balance romance with ambition.

title: The Notebook (2004)
description: A young couple falls in love during the early 1940s; years later, their affair is re-awakened when one of them reads their own love story from a notebook.

title: Inception (2010)
description: A skilled thief who steals corporate secrets by entering people's dreams is given a chance at redemption if he can successfully perform 'inception.'

title: Interstellar (2014)
description: A team of explorers travels through a wormhole in space to ensure humanity's survival as Earth faces catastrophic crop failures and dust storms.
